        <Classification DateLastEvaluated="2015-08-08">
          <ReviewStatus>criteria provided, single submitter</ReviewStatus>
          <GermlineClassification>Likely pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment Type="public">This sequence change deletes 1 nucleotide from exon 12 of the SMAD4 mRNA (c.1512delT), causing a frameshift at codon 505. This creates a premature translational stop signal in the last exon of the SMAD4 mRNA (p.Phe505Leufs*2). While this is not anticipated to result in nonsense mediated decay, it is expected to result in a truncated SMAD4 protein. While this particular sequence change has not been reported in the literature, truncating sequence changes in SMAD4 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 22810475, 16152648). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Likely Pathogenic.</Comment>
        </Classification>
